<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[794,1418,1050,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,1066,1050,1075]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Differential diagnosis:</emphasis>
Pronotum subquadrate, pale brown at lateral margins, with wide median dark-brown patch; elytra entirely dark brown; males: fore femur slightly swollen, with distinct, sharp, ventral tooth; ventrite VIII with short transverse lateral ridge near left margin, and elongate, oblique longitudinal median ridge; aedeagus with right prolongation of tegmen truncate, short and narrow; left setiferous prolongation absent; females: ventrite VII short, wide, lateral margins arched, posterior margin projected, with three small lobes at apex. 
<taxonomicName authority="Biffi &amp; Constantin, 2018" authorityName="Biffi &amp; Constantin" authorityYear="2018" box="[871,1173,1370,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Macromalthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xerophilus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[871,1173,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Macromalthinus xerophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1191,1287,1370,1395]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pic, 1906)" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[794,1068,1402,1427]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Maronius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis box="[794,944,1402,1427]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">M. brasiliensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pic, M." box="[958,1061,1402,1427]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="9 - 12" refId="ref19026" refString="Pic, M. 1906. Nouveaux coleopteres d'Europe, Asie, Afrique et Amerique. L'Echange, Revue Linneenne, 22 (254): 9 - 12." type="journal article" year="1906">Pic, 1906</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
but differs by the smaller size, darker colour and particular characters of aedeagus,ventrites VII and VIII of males and ventrite VII of females.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[794,1418,1050,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Besides the size and colour, 
<taxonomicName authority="Biffi &amp; Constantin, 2018" authorityName="Biffi &amp; Constantin" authorityYear="2018" box="[1142,1284,1498,1523]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Macromalthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xerophilus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1142,1284,1498,1523]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">M. xerophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1290,1375,1498,1523]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[898,1047,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Maronius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis box="[898,1047,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">M. brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the fore femur of males with a stronger and sharper ventral tooth, and posterior margin of ventrite VII of females more prominent, forming small rounded lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[794,1418,1690,1971]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,1040,1690,1715]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Description: Length:</emphasis>
5.3-6.0 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1199,1347,1690,1715]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Colouration:</emphasis>
Head black, clypeus and mandibles dark brown; antennae dark brown, lighter on antennomeres I-III and IX-XI; labial and maxillary palpi light brown; pronotum pale brown laterally, with wide median dark brown patch; elytra, wings, thorax and abdomen dark brown; legs pale brown, dark- er on dorsal surface of femora and apex of tibiae and tarsi; ventrites I-VI light brown, tergites and ventrite VII dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[878,940,1946,1971]" captionStart="Figures 1-6" captionStartId="3.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[152,1356,206,2041]" captionTargetId="figure-1@3.[151,1360,204,2044]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 1-6:Dorsal habitus ofMacromalthinus species.(1) M.guyanensis sp.nov.(2)M.luteoapicalissp.nov.(3)M.orapuensis sp.nov.(4) M.piceiventrissp.nov. (5) M.quadratithorax sp.nov.(6)M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384149/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[794,1418,2010,2131]" lastBlockId="14.[170,795,218,1331]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,870,2010,2035]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Males:</emphasis>
Head large, 1.2 times wider than the pronotum, temples elongate, strongly tapering posteriorly, vertex concave. Eyes large, oblong, very prominent. Antennae filiform, slightly flattened dorso-ventrally, covered with thick short setae; antennomere I elongate, wider apically, II very short, 0.5 the length of I, III slightly longer than II, IV-XI nearly the same length as I. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[676,749,282,307]" captionStart="Figures 7-12" captionStartId="4.[869,937,1217,1242]" captionTargetBox="[869,1493,204,1187]" captionTargetId="figure-697@4.[869,1493,204,1187]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figures 7-12: Pronotum of Macromalthinus species. (7) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (8) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (9) M. orapuensis sp. nov. (10) M. piceiventris sp. nov. (11) M. quadratithorax sp. nov. (12) M. xerophilus sp. nov. Scale bars:1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384151/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) 1.1 times wider than long; anterior margin slightly arched, lateral margins nearly parallel, slightly constricted near anterior angles; pronotal surface elevated antero-medially and near posterior angles, forming two lateral shallow grooves convergent posteriorly. Elytra short, rugulose, densely covered with short and thin setae; sutures broadly dehiscent from posterior half; apex swollen dorsally. Legs slender; fore femur (
<figureCitation box="[522,598,538,563]" captionStart="Figures 13-18" captionStartId="5.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[97,1416,991,2040]" captionTargetId="figure-354@5.[94,1417,986,2044]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 13-18: Fore femur of Macromalthinus species. (13) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (14) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov.(15) M. orapuensis sp.nov.(16) M. piceiventris sp.nov.(17) M. quadratithoraxsp.nov.(18) M. xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384153" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384153/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) slightly swollen, with a distinct, sharp, ventral tooth; femora, tibiae and tarsomeres increasing in length from fore to hind legs. Tarsal claws simple, not toothed. Abdominal tergites and sternites sclerotized, densely covered with long and thick setae; glandular pores not prominent; posterior margin of ventrites I-V overlapping the base of subsequent ones; ventrite VI broadly notched, membranous posteriorly; ventrite VII (
<figureCitation box="[429,503,794,819]" captionStart="Figures 19-24" captionStartId="6.[170,238,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[172,1491,1272,2042]" captionTargetId="figure-506@6.[170,1493,1269,2044]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 19-24:Ventrite VII of males of Macromalthinus species.(19) M.guyanensis sp.nov.(20) M.luteoapicalis sp.nov.(21)M. orapuensis sp.nov.(22) M.piceiventris sp.nov.(23) M.quadratithorax sp.nov.(24) M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384156/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
) H-shaped,lateral margins roundly emarginated, with deep and wide membranous area anteriorly, wide and broadly arched posterior notch; ventrite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[308,383,890,915]" captionStart="Figures 25-30" captionStartId="7.[794,862,2010,2035]" captionTargetBox="[798,1414,205,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-491@7.[794,1418,204,1980]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 25-30: Ventrite VIII of males of Macromalthinus species. (25) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (26) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (27) M. orapuensis sp.nov.(28)M.piceiventrissp.nov.(29) M.quadratithoraxsp.nov.(30) M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384158" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384158/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) asymmetrical, oblong, strongly convex; short transverse lateral ridge near left margin, long oblique longitudinal median ridge. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[709,788,954,979]" captionStart="Figures 31-36" captionStartId="8.[170,238,2042,2067]" captionTargetBox="[171,1491,674,2008]" captionTargetId="figure-183@8.[170,1493,670,2012]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 31-36: Aedeagus of Macromalthinus species. (31) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (32) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (33) M. orapuensis sp. nov. (34) M. piceiventris sp.nov.(35) M. quadratithorax sp.nov.(36) M. xerophilus sp.nov. Abbreviations:pt = prolongation of tegmen, sp = setiferous prolongation,rp = right paramere, lp = left paramere,ml = median lobe.Scale bars:0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384160/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) with right prolongation of tegmen truncate, short, narrow, without apophysis on dorsal surface; left setiferous prolongation absent; right paramere elongate, flat, apex acute; left paramere elongate, flat,apex rounded, partially covering dorsal surface of median lobe; median lobe straight with long apical membranous surface dorsally. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,504,1178,1203]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Measurements of 
<typeStatus box="[389,500,1178,1203]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">holotype</typeStatus>
:
