</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[170,795,1370,1811]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,263,1370,1395]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Female:</emphasis>
similar to males; eyes smaller, less prominent; fore femora slender, without intumescence or tooth; abdomen less sclerotized; ventrite VI entire, not notched posteriorly; ventrite VII (
<figureCitation box="[438,514,1466,1491]" captionStart="Figures 37-42" captionStartId="9.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[94,1414,1424,2040]" captionTargetId="figure-592@9.[94,1417,1420,2044]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 37-42:VentriteVII offemales ofMacromalthinusspecies.(37) M.guyanensis sp.nov.(38)M.luteoapicalissp.nov.(39) M.orapuensissp.nov.(40)M.piceiventris sp.nov.(41) M. quadratithoraxsp.nov.(42) M. xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384162/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
) short, wide, lateral margins arched, posterior margin prominent, with three small lobes at middle; coxites (
<figureCitation box="[523,601,1530,1555]" captionStart="Figures 43-48" captionStartId="10.[869,937,2010,2035]" captionTargetBox="[873,1490,1055,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-666@10.[869,1493,1054,1980]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figures 43-48: Coxites of Macromalthinus species. (43) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (44) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (45) M. orapuensis sp. nov. (46) M. piceiventris sp. nov. (47) M. quadratithorax sp. nov. (48) M. xerophilus sp. nov. Scale bars:0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384164" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384164/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
) with base elongate, slender, apex very short, with a broad projection behind styles bearing few thin setae; styles elongate, slightly wider apically, bearing thick and long setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,754,1658,1683]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Measurements of medium size female 
<typeStatus box="[640,751,1658,1683]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">paratype</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
TL: 6.0; AL: 4.8; OL: 0.51; HW: 1.12; IOW: 0.57; IAW: 0.2; PL: 0.86; PW: 0.93; EL: 1.8; EW: 1.24. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Length of each antennomere:</emphasis>
aI: 0.37; aII: 0.18; aIII: 0.30; aIV: 0.43; aV: 0.45; aVI: 0.47; aVII: 0.47; aVIII: 0.48; aIX: 0.48; aX: 0.43; aXI: 0.46.
</paragraph>
