<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[170,794,1850,1907]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,306,1850,1875]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet is allusive to the dry climate of the 
<typeStatus box="[303,353,1882,1907]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
locality (Caruaru).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[170,708,1946,1971]" box="[170,708,1946,1971]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,321,1946,1971]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[327,387,1946,1971]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[398,604,1946,1971]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Pernambuco state</collectingRegion>
) (
<figureCitation box="[621,698,1946,1971]" captionStart="Figures 66-69" captionStartId="19.[94,162,2042,2067]" captionTargetBox="[151,1360,431,2012]" captionTargetId="figure-79@19.[151,1360,431,2012]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figures 66-69: Distribution of Macromalthinus species. (66) Distribution of Macromalthinus species in South America. (67) Distribution of M. brasiliensis in Brazil.(68)Distribution ofM.maximiceps inFrench Guiana.(69)Distribution of M.guyanensis sp.nov.,andM.orapuensis sp.nov.inFrench Guiana.Background maps of Figs.66-67 by NaturalEarth (available at:www.naturalearthdata.com), and Figs.68-69 byEric Gaba." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384172" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384172/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[170,794,2010,2131]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,410,2010,2035]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Locality description:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Biffi &amp; Constantin, 2018" authorityName="Biffi &amp; Constantin" authorityYear="2018" box="[415,555,2010,2035]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Macromalthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xerophilus" status="sp.nov.">
<emphasis box="[415,555,2010,2035]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">M.xerophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[560,643,2010,2035]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="species">sp.nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is recorded in the 
<emphasis box="[211,291,2042,2067]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Agreste</emphasis>
region,a transition zone between the Atlantic forest and the semiarid Caatinga biome in Northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[170,232,2106,2131]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The vegetation in the Agreste at Caruaru is char-
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[869,1493,218,275]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
acterized as arboreal deciduous thorny vegetation (
<bibRefCitation author="Alcoforado-Filho, F. G. &amp; Sampaio, E. V. S. B. &amp; Rodal, M. J. N." box="[875,1188,250,275]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="287 - 303" refId="ref18297" refString="Alcoforado-Filho, F. G.; Sampaio, E. V. S. B. &amp; Rodal, M. J. N. 2003. Floristica e fitossociologia de um remanescente de vegetacao caducifolia espinhosa arborea em Caruaru, Pernambuco. Acta Botanica Brasilica, 17 (2): 287 - 303. DOI" type="journal article" year="2003">
Alcoforado-Filho 
<emphasis box="[1067,1124,250,275]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al.,</emphasis>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
